articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Israeli military strikes across the Palestinian Gaza Strip killed at least 61 people in the space of 24 hours, local medics said on Saturday, as Israeli forces battled Hamas-led militants in the territory.
articles.title: Israeli strikes in Gaza kill 61 as UN pursues vaccinations

articles.author: Max Hunder
articles.description: Ukraine's air force said on Saturday Russia launched a total of 67 long-range Shahed drones in a mass overnight attack, 58 of which it was able to shoot down.
articles.title: Ukraine says Russia launched 67 drones in overnight attack

articles.author: Luc Cohen
articles.description: A New York judge on Friday delayed former U.S. President Donald Trump's sentencing on charges stemming from hush money paid to a porn star until after the Nov. 5 election.
articles.title: Judge delays Trump hush money sentencing until after election

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: British tech tycoon Mike Lynch died of suffocation after running out of oxygen, an investigative source said, citing initial examinations carried out on Saturday after his body was recovered from the family yacht that sank off Sicily's coast last month.
articles.title: Autopsy suggests tycoon Mike Lynch likely died of suffocation in yacht, source says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A political adviser to Iraqi Prime Minister Mohammed Shia al-Sudani has rejected recent allegations that employees at the premier's office have been spying on and wire-tapping senior officials and politicians.
articles.title: No spying took place by employees of Iraqi prime minister's office, adviser says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Super Typhoon Yagi, Asia's most powerful storm this year, churned towards the northern coast of Vietnam on Saturday after tearing through China's southern island province of Hainan with lightning, rain and violent winds.
articles.title: Super Typhoon Yagi sets sight on Vietnam after tearing through China's Hainan

articles.author: John Irish
articles.description: Thousands of people took to the streets across France on Saturday to protest President Emmanuel Macron's decision to appoint centre-right Michel Barnier as prime minister with left-wing parties accusing him of stealing legislative elections.
articles.title: Thousands protest in France after Macron picks Barnier as prime minister

articles.author: Lisandra Paraguassu
articles.description: Venezuela informed Brazil that it revoked an authorization to represent Argentine interests in the country, including administering the embassy where six opposition figures are sheltering, a Brazilian diplomatic source said on Saturday.
articles.title: Venezuela revokes authorization for Brazil to represent Argentine interests in the country, source says

articles.author: Duncan Miriri, Laurie Chen
articles.description: China stopped short of providing the debt relief sought by many African countries this week, but pledged 360 billion yuan ($50.7 billion) over three years in credit lines and investments.
articles.title: China stops short of Africa debt relief as pledges more cash

articles.author: Joshua McElwee
articles.description: Pope Francis on Saturday called for better treatment of workers in Papua New Guinea, a nation of some 600 islands in the Southwestern Pacific that has become a major target of international companies for its gas, gold and other reserves.
articles.title: Pope Francis, in resource-rich Papua New Guinea, urges fair treatment for workers
